  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "3D Designer (Events)",
  "description": "<p>Twist Media is made up of a team of experienced and passionate professionals who are committed to creating events that matter.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Our team is currently expanding and we are looking for a talented and motivated 3D Event Designer to join us. We need someone who is quick thinking with a passion for events and enjoys working in a fun environment.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>If you understand Experiential Design – we want to hear from you!</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>This is what we would like to see in you:</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Great attitude and takes pride in your work</li>\n  <li>Ability to see a project from idea generation, concept development, through to final output</li>\n  <li>Ability to tailor creative thinking and approach to best serve project objectives and client needs</li>\n  <li>Ability to translate design ideas into 3D renderings and construction drawings for client presentations and productions</li>\n  <li>Ability to work quickly, efficiently, and calmly under pressure</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently or in support of all or any creative/project department members</li>\n  <li>A thorough understanding of layout and visual communication theory</li>\n  <li>Have a strong flair for innovative display solutions</li>\n  <li>A high degree of proficiency in Autodesk 3ds Max, Adobe Creative Cloud softwares – Illustrator, InDesign and Photoshop as a minimum</li>\n  <li>Experience in the exhibition, events or related industries will be highly-valued</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>You will join a tight knit team in a progressive agency that rewards great work and encourages work-life balance.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>If you are keen on working in a fast-paced team, understand experiential design, is committed to demonstrating critical and creative thinking, as well as pushing technical boundaries, come say hello to us.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Please submit your <strong>portfolio</strong> together with your resume. Thanks.</p>",
